cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MS, cs.IR

The paper deals with the use of deep convolutional neural networks for the classification of melanoma and nevus images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and the customization of batch logic and loss function in the model architecture also suggest the relevance of these sub-categories. The paper also involves the use of a large dataset and the comparison of model performance to that of dermatologists, which could potentially fall under the sub-categories of information retrieval (cs.IR) and medical imaging (cs.MS).
